{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1801,"text":"There is nothing bigger\nor older than the universe."},{"time":7500,"text":"The questions\nI would like to talk about are:"},{"time":13349,"text":"one, where did we come from?"},{"time":17817,"text":"How did the universe come into being?"},{"time":22007,"text":"Are we alone in the universe?"},{"time":24993,"text":"Is there alien life out there?"},{"time":28136,"text":"What is the future of the human race?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":31446,"text":"Up until the 1920s,"},{"time":34000,"text":"everyone thought the universe\nwas essentially static"},{"time":37000,"text":"and unchanging in time."},{"time":40062,"text":"Then it was discovered\nthat the universe was expanding."},{"time":44681,"text":"Distant galaxies were moving away from us."},{"time":49504,"text":"This meant they must have been\ncloser together in the past."},{"time":54253,"text":"If we extrapolate back,"},{"time":56380,"text":"we find we must have\nall been on top of each other"},{"time":60000,"text":"about 15 billion years ago."},{"time":63696,"text":"This was the Big Bang,\nthe beginning of the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68506,"text":"But was there anything\nbefore the Big Bang?"},{"time":72483,"text":"If not, what created the universe?"},{"time":76323,"text":"Why did the universe emerge\nfrom the Big Bang the way it did?"},{"time":82190,"text":"We used to think\nthat the theory of the universe"},{"time":85000,"text":"could be divided into two parts."},{"time":88510,"text":"First, there were the laws"},{"time":90000,"text":"like Maxwell's equations\nand general relativity"},{"time":93688,"text":"that determined the evolution\nof the universe,"},{"time":96677,"text":"given its state\nover all of space at one time."},{"time":101308,"text":"And second, there was no question\nof the initial state of the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107751,"text":"We have made good progress\non the first part,"},{"time":111000,"text":"and now have the knowledge\nof the laws of evolution"},{"time":114000,"text":"in all but the most extreme conditions."},{"time":117000,"text":"But until recently,\nwe have had little idea"},{"time":120000,"text":"about the initial conditions\nfor the universe."},{"time":124237,"text":"However, this division into laws\nof evolution and initial conditions"},{"time":129690,"text":"depends on time and space\nbeing separate and distinct."},{"time":134674,"text":"Under extreme conditions,\ngeneral relativity and quantum theory"},{"time":139499,"text":"allow time to behave\nlike another dimension of space."},{"time":147612,"text":"This removes the distinction\nbetween time and space,"},{"time":151223,"text":"and means the laws of evolution\ncan also determine the initial state."},{"time":159410,"text":"The universe can spontaneously\ncreate itself out of nothing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166597,"text":"Moreover, we can calculate\na probability that the universe"},{"time":171000,"text":"was created in different states."},{"time":174433,"text":"These predictions\nare in excellent agreement"},{"time":176786,"text":"with observations by the WMAP satellite\nof the cosmic microwave background,"},{"time":182982,"text":"which is an imprint\nof the very early universe."},{"time":187890,"text":"We think we have solved\nthe mystery of creation."},{"time":192236,"text":"Maybe we should patent the universe"},{"time":194792,"text":"and charge everyone royalties\nfor their existence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201402,"text":"I now turn to the second big question:"},{"time":204378,"text":"are we alone, or is there\nother life in the universe?"},{"time":212000,"text":"We believe that life arose\nspontaneously on the Earth,"},{"time":215689,"text":"so it must be possible for life\nto appear on other suitable planets,"},{"time":220563,"text":"of which there seem to be\na large number in the galaxy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226728,"text":"But we don't know how life first appeared."},{"time":232104,"text":"We have two pieces\nof observational evidence"},{"time":235000,"text":"on the probability of life appearing."},{"time":239902,"text":"The first is that we have fossils of algae\nfrom 3.5 billion years ago."},{"time":247000,"text":"The Earth was formed 4.6 billion years ago"},{"time":251180,"text":"and was probably too hot\nfor about the first half billion years."},{"time":261430,"text":"So life appeared on Earth"},{"time":263279,"text":"within half a billion years\nof it being possible,"},{"time":266955,"text":"which is short compared\nto the 10-billion-year lifetime"},{"time":270655,"text":"of a planet of Earth type."},{"time":273424,"text":"This suggests that the probability\nof life appearing is reasonably high."},{"time":279266,"text":"If it was very low,\none would have expected it"},{"time":282518,"text":"to take most\nof the ten billion years available."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287010,"text":"On the other hand, we don't seem\nto have been visited by aliens."},{"time":292698,"text":"I am discounting the reports of UFOs."},{"time":296658,"text":"Why would they appear\nonly to cranks and weirdos?"},{"time":302477,"text":"If there is a government conspiracy\nto suppress the reports"},{"time":306566,"text":"and keep for itself the scientific\nknowledge the aliens bring,"},{"time":311000,"text":"it seems to have been a singularly\nineffective policy so far."},{"time":320286,"text":"Furthermore, despite an extensive search\nby the SETI project,"},{"time":325000,"text":"we haven't heard any alien\ntelevision quiz shows."},{"time":330134,"text":"This probably indicates\nthat there are no alien civilizations"},{"time":334445,"text":"at our stage of development"},{"time":336715,"text":"within a radius\nof a few hundred light years."},{"time":341000,"text":"Issuing an insurance policy"},{"time":343000,"text":"against abduction by aliens\nseems a pretty safe bet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350109,"text":"This brings me to the last\nof the big questions:"},{"time":353419,"text":"the future of the human race."},{"time":356661,"text":"If we are the only intelligent\nbeings in the galaxy,"},{"time":360344,"text":"we should make sure\nwe survive and continue."},{"time":366840,"text":"But we are entering an increasingly\ndangerous period of our history."},{"time":375964,"text":"Our population and our use\nof the finite resources of planet Earth"},{"time":380822,"text":"are growing exponentially,"},{"time":382918,"text":"along with our technical ability\nto change the environment for good or ill."},{"time":392709,"text":"But our genetic code"},{"time":394479,"text":"still carries the selfish\nand aggressive instincts"},{"time":397510,"text":"that were of survival\nadvantage in the past."},{"time":404931,"text":"It will be difficult enough\nto avoid disaster"},{"time":407976,"text":"in the next hundred years,"},{"time":409716,"text":"let alone the next thousand or million."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416507,"text":"Our only chance of long-term survival"},{"time":419642,"text":"is not to remain inward-looking\non planet Earth,"},{"time":423000,"text":"but to spread out into space."},{"time":428000,"text":"The answers to these big questions"},{"time":430444,"text":"show that we have made remarkable progress\nin the last hundred years."},{"time":436296,"text":"But if we want to continue\nbeyond the next hundred years,"},{"time":440343,"text":"our future is in space."},{"time":444563,"text":"That is why I am in favor of manned --"},{"time":447000,"text":"or should I say, \npersonned -- space flight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455906,"text":"All of my life I have sought\nto understand the universe"},{"time":460000,"text":"and find answers to these questions."},{"time":463505,"text":"I have been very lucky"},{"time":465362,"text":"that my disability has not been\na serious handicap."},{"time":469443,"text":"Indeed, it has probably given me\nmore time than most people"},{"time":474106,"text":"to pursue the quest for knowledge."},{"time":480006,"text":"The ultimate goal is a complete\ntheory of the universe,"},{"time":484000,"text":"and we are making good progress."},{"time":490159,"text":"Thank you for listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494460,"text":"Chris Anderson: Professor,\nif you had to guess either way,"},{"time":497838,"text":"do you now believe\nthat it is more likely than not"},{"time":501668,"text":"that we are alone in the Milky Way,"},{"time":505010,"text":"as a civilization of our level\nof intelligence or higher?"},{"time":525000,"text":"This answer took seven minutes,\nand really gave me an insight"},{"time":531000,"text":"into the incredible act of generosity\nthis whole talk was for TED."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546483,"text":"Stephen Hawking: I think it quite likely\nthat we are the only civilization"},{"time":551000,"text":"within several hundred light years;"},{"time":554359,"text":"otherwise we would have heard radio waves."},{"time":560472,"text":"The alternative is that civilizations\ndon't last very long,"},{"time":564976,"text":"but destroy themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568670,"text":"CA: Professor Hawking,\nthank you for that answer."},{"time":572000,"text":"We will take it\nas a salutary warning, I think,"},{"time":574973,"text":"for the rest of our conference this week."},{"time":578101,"text":"Professor, we really thank you\nfor the extraordinary effort you made"},{"time":582291,"text":"to share your questions with us today."},{"time":585228,"text":"Thank you very much indeed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586904,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}